    "Name": "Rhino Fire Support Tank",
    "Details": "Designed in 2667, the Rhino was intended as a far more heavily armored version of the ubiquitous LRM Carrier. While carrying one less 20 tube launcher, the Rhino is covered in seventeen tons of armor, a whopping fifteen more than a Quik-based carrier can boast. Designed to anchor defensive lines, the Rhino mounts two  LRM-20 launchers alongside a pair  of Medium Lasers in its turret, supported by a single  LRM-10 mounted forward. The vehicle's total of four tons of LRM reloads compare favourably with the standard carrier, while the lasers allow it some defensive ability while retreating to rearm; however, the vehicle's extremely slow speed greatly hampers any retreat once engaged in battle.\n\n <b><color=#ffcc00>Tracked: High traction, agile turning.</color></b>\n\n <b><color=#ffcc00>Fusion: Expensive engine that works in a Vacuum.</color></b>\n\n <b><color=#ffcc00>Movement: 3/5 Hex: 90/120 Meters.</color></b>\n\n<b>Armor:</b> Armor\n<b>Structure:</b> Structure\n<b>Values       A        S  </b>\n<b>Front</b>       320     40\n<b>Left</b>         270     40\n<b>Right</b>       270     40\n<b>Rear</b>        200     40\n<b>Turret</b>      300     40\n\n<b>Total</b>      1360    200\n",
